  "conclusion": "Forcing the full-attention context+gate branch and O projection together to per-row diagnostics is not a safe rowchunk fix. It removes the rowchunk3 L6 generated-token failure (rowchunk3 token_passed=true) but leaves rowchunk3 hidden/projection/stage drift (L5 layer4 QKV/Z drift and L8 layer7 attn_input_pre_qkv/attn_context failures), while the rowchunk2 control becomes token-red at L8 and gains QKV/Z drift under the per-row O suffix. The combined context/gate+O suffix is therefore eliminated as a retained-compatible fix; the useful signal is that the rowchunk3 token failure can be moved by the O-bearing suffix, but not without poisoning rowchunk2 or fixing the inherited hidden trajectory.",
